AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 626 House Bill No. 457*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-7-112(e)(10), is amended by
deleting the last sentence and substituting instead:
If the county election commission determines that the counting of provisional
ballots cannot be completed by the designated time, the state coordinator of
elections may grant the county an extension of time and shall designate a time
that is no later than the third Monday after the election.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-7-112(a)(3)(B)(i), is amended by
adding the following to the end of the subdivision:
The county election commission shall publish a notice of the location of the
provisional counting board in conjunction with the notice of election required by §
2-12-111(c) and shall not change the location except in the event of an
emergency.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-9-110, is amended by adding the
following as new subsections:
(d) The county election commission shall not tabulate any marked ballots
submitted via the internet.
(e) Voting machines are prohibited from being connected to the internet.
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-2-106(c)(2), is amended by adding
the following to the end of the subdivision:
