The county election commission shall also follow this process if indications exist
that the voter may no longer reside at the address at which the voter is
registered, such as the voter's failure to vote, or otherwise update the voter's
registration over a period of two (2) consecutive regular November elections.
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-2-118(a), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting instead:
(a) A person who registers to vote in the county election commission office shall
present evidence of identification or verification of residential address, as those terms
are defined in § 2-7-112.
SECTION 6. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-2-111, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(f) A registration form from a person who registers to vote at a supplemental
registration who does not present evidence of identification or verification of residential
address, as those terms are defined in § 2-7-112, must be processed in accordance with
§ 2-2-115.
SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-2-124(a), is amended by adding
the following to the end of the subsection:
The administrator of elections shall mail the voter registration card to any new
voter who has not provided verification of residential address, as defined in § 2-7-
112, or who registers at a supplemental registration held pursuant to § 2-2-111.
SECTION 8. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-2-132, is amended by deleting the
section and substituting instead:
The commission shall purge the permanent registration records of those persons
whose registrations are required to be purged under § 2-2-106, unless otherwise
prohibited by federal law.
SECTION 9. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
